 {"id": "franken_networkx-multikeyrt", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] MultiGraph round-trip through node_link_data / _from_nx_graph lost string keys", "description": "MultiGraph with edges keyed by non-integer values (strings, tuples) round-tripped through fnx.node_link_data/graph or fnx.readwrite._from_nx_graph would lose the original keys \u2014 fnx reassigned fresh integer keys. The Rust binding now accepts arbitrary keys directly, so removed the non-int fallback and preserve nx keys verbatim. Regression-visible: fnx.node_link_graph(data) now returns edges with original string keys instead of [0, 1, ...].", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T11:56:43.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T11:56:43.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T11:56:43.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Remove non-int fallback; Rust MultiGraph binding now accepts arbitrary keys", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-triadnode", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] triadic_census missing nodelist kwarg", "description": "nx.triadic_census(G, nodelist=[...]) restricts the count to triads touching at least one node in the list. fnx.triadic_census accepted only (G). Added nodelist parameter; delegates to nx when nodelist is non-None since the Rust native does not yet filter.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Added nodelist kwarg with nx delegation", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-triadkw", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] triad_graph used triad_type_str instead of nx triad_name", "description": "fnx.triad_graph named first param triad_type_str while nx uses triad_name. Kwarg-style drop-in calls failed. Renamed.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T11:58:47.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Param rename", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-boundkw", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] cut_size/normalized_cut_size/node_boundary/is_chordal/chordal_graph_cliques/is_biconnected used g and nbunch1/nbunch2", "description": "Several boundary and predicate functions re-exported the Rust binding directly which used lowercase g and (for cut ops) nbunch1/nbunch2 instead of nx G/S/T. Drop-in kwarg-style calls TypeErrored. Added Python wrappers with nx-matching parameter names and updated internal edge_expansion/mixing_expansion callers to use T= instead of nbunch2=.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Python wrappers with G/S/T names", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-edgebounddata", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_boundary missing data/keys/default kwargs", "description": "nx.edge_boundary(G, nbunch1, data=True) emits (u, v, attrs) tuples; fnx accepted only (G, nbunch1, nbunch2). Added data/keys/default via delegation to nx when any is non-default; fast-path kept for the common case.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:22.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Added data/keys/default kwargs with nx delegation", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
